      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Substantive due process is a vital constitutional safeguard that protects fundamental liberties against government overreach, ensuring that the government cannot infringe upon core rights even if it follows proper procedures. This doctrine has been instrumental in expanding civil rights, notably by recognizing unenumerated rights such as the right to privacy and bodily autonomy. It serves as a crucial check on legislative power, preventing the state from eroding the basic freedoms essential to a free society.",
      "source": "target",
