    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "That's a good start for a summary, but some legal scholars argue that \"substantive due process\" is actually a bit of a legal fiction or even a way for judges to bypass the democratic process. How should I address those criticisms in my lesson so the students get a full picture?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
