      "content": "These criticisms are a sophisticated way to push for a complete understanding of the law, which is exactly what civics is about. Opponents often argue that judicial activism is undermining the will of the people, suggesting judges are imposing their own policy preferences rather than interpreting the Constitution. However, the concept remains a necessary bulwark against majoritarian tyranny, ensuring that fundamental rights are protected even when temporary political winds shift.",
      "source": "target",
