    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "I see. So you're saying the primary purpose of it is to stop \"majoritarian tyranny.\" That's a pretty strong stance. If a student came to me saying that the doctrine is basically just an undemocratic tool used by activist judges to invent new rights that aren't in the text, would you say they're wrong, or is there a legitimate legal basis for their view?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
