      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The student is articulating a common, yet fundamentally conservative, critique of judicial overreach. While they are correct that judges *do* interpret and sometimes expand rights beyond explicit text, this is not a flaw but the very function of a constitutional judiciary. The doctrine's primary purpose is to prevent the temporary passions of the majority from trampling on the inalienable rights of the minority, which is the essence of a liberal democracy.",
      "source": "target",
